Shefa-Amr

*   שפרעם
*   شفاعمرو

A [City](/List_of_cities_in_Israel) of [Arab citizens of Israel](/Arab_citizens_of_Israel) in the [Northern District](/Northern_District_(Israel)) of [Israel](/Israel), Shefa-Amr, or Shefar'am, exists not merely as a dot on a map but as a layered testament to millennia of human habitation and the predictable cycles of power, conflict, and coexistence. Its very existence, a vibrant [Arab city](/Arab_citizens_of_Israel) within the modern state of [Israel](/Israel), is a subtle defiance to simple categorization.

**Hebrew transcription(s)**
*   [ISO 259](/ISO_259) Šparˁam
*   English Official Shefar'am

